  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "1. Tool Overview",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Description: WhatWeb is a next-generation web scanner that identifies technologies used by websites including content management systems (CMS), blogging platforms, statistic/analytics packages, JavaScript libraries, web servers, and embedded devices.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Category: Reconnaissance, Fingerprinting, Information Gathering",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Developer/Maintainer: Andrew Horton (urbanadventurer) and the WhatWeb contributors",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "License: GNU General Public License v2.0 (GPL-2.0)",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Official Resources:",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "GitHub Repository",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Wiki",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Official Website",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "2. Installation Guide",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "System Requirements:",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Operating Systems: Linux, macOS, Windows (with Ruby)",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Ruby 2.x or newer",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Dependencies: ruby-dev, libcurl4-openssl-dev, make, zlib1g-dev, liblzma-dev",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Installation Methods:",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Using Git: bashgit clone https://github.com/urbanadventurer/whatweb.git",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "cd whatweb",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "bundle install",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "On Kali Linux/Debian/Ubuntu: bashapt-get update",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "apt-get install whatweb",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Using Ruby Gems: bashgem install whatweb",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Docker Installation: bashdocker pull urbanadventurer/whatweb",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "docker run -it urbanadventurer/whatweb whatweb example.com",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Verification: bashwhatweb --version",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "3. Basic Configuration",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Initial Setup: No specific initial setup required after installation.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Configuration Files:",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Plugin files located in <installation_path>/plugins/",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Custom plugins can be added to the plugins directory",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Environment Variables: No specific environment variables required.",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Default Credentials: Not applicable (no authentication needed for the tool itself)",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "4. Core Functionality",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Key Features:",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Identifies web technologies, including CMS, blogging platforms, analytics packages",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Over 1800 plugins for fingerprinting",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Supports multiple targets and recursive website spidering",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Configurable aggression levels (stealth to aggressive)",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Plugin system for easy customization",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Various output formats (JSON, XML, SQL, etc.)",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Ability to scan through proxies or use custom user agents",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Batch mode for scanning multiple targets",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Basic Usage: bashwhatweb https://example.com",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Command Structure: whatweb [options] <target> Where:",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "options are various command-line flags",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "<target> is a URL, IP address, IP range, or filename containing targets",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Common Parameters:",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "-a - Aggression level (1-4, higher = more aggressive)",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "-v - Verbose output",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "-i - Take input from a file",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "-o - Output to file",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "--log-json - Log in JSON format",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "--log-xml - Log in XML format",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "--log-sql - Log in SQL format",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "--user-agent - Set custom user agent",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "--max-threads - Set maximum number of threads",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "--proxy - Use proxy server",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "--grep - Search for string in the results",
    "images": []
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "",
    "images": []
  },
